# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Erika Card Tracker — environment configuration
#
# Copy this file to `.env` for LOCAL development (`.env` is git-ignored).
# For the deployed site, set these as ENVIRONMENT SECRETS on the GitHub
# "production" environment (Settings → Environments) — see SETUP.md.
#
# NOTE: anything prefixed VITE_ is bundled into the shipped site and is visible
# to anyone who views the page source. That's expected for a static site — the
# real access control is that the Apps Script Web App only exposes read + a
# single owned-toggle. Do NOT put a Google service-account key here; it isn't
# needed and would be exposed.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# The deployment URL of your Google Apps Script Web App (ends in /exec).
# Replace REPLACE_WITH_DEPLOYMENT_ID with your real deployment id.
# While this still contains REPLACE_WITH_DEPLOYMENT_ID the app shows a
# "connect your sheet" screen instead of trying to load.
VITE_SHEETS_API_URL=https://script.google.com/macros/s/REPLACE_WITH_DEPLOYMENT_ID/exec

# Optional soft write-gate. Leave BLANK for open access (recommended for a
# personal tracker). If you set it, use the SAME value for SHARED_TOKEN in
# apps-script/Code.gs so the app is allowed to save.
VITE_SHEETS_API_TOKEN=

# Optional edit passcode. Leave BLANK to disable the lock entirely (checkboxes
# stay editable for everyone, same as before). If set, the site loads with
# owned-status editing LOCKED behind a lock icon (top right of the header) —
# visitors can browse and search, but toggling a checkbox requires entering
# this passcode first. Once entered correctly it's remembered on that device
# (localStorage) until someone taps the lock again to re-lock.
#
# Like VITE_SHEETS_API_TOKEN above, this ships inside the built JS by nature
# of a static site — it's a UI deterrent against casual/accidental edits (e.g.
# someone else picking up your phone), NOT real security. Don't reuse a
# passcode you use anywhere sensitive.
VITE_EDIT_PASSCODE=

# ── Deploy-time card sync (CI only — NOT a VITE_ var, never bundled) ─────────
# The GitHub Actions deploy pushes this repo's card list into the sheet while
# preserving owned status. In CI these come from the `production` environment
# secrets VITE_SHEETS_API_URL and SHEETS_SYNC_TOKEN. To run the sync by hand
# locally, set these (SHEETS_SYNC_TOKEN must match ADMIN_TOKEN in Code.gs):
#   SHEETS_API_URL=https://script.google.com/macros/s/REPLACE_WITH_DEPLOYMENT_ID/exec
#   SHEETS_SYNC_TOKEN=your-strong-admin-token
#   node scripts/sync-sheet.mjs
